select count(*) as aggregate from `listings` where `id` = '1'

select `listings`.*, (select count(*) from `users` inner join `listing_users` on `users`.`id` = `listing_users`.`user_id` where `listings`.`id` = `listing_users`.`listing_id`) as `users_count`, exists(select * from `users` inner join `listing_users` on `users`.`id` = `listing_users`.`user_id` where `listings`.`id` = `listing_users`.`listing_id` and `users`.`id` = 5) as `is_liked` from `listings` where `status` = 'active' and `listings`.`id` = '1' limit 1

select `amenities`.*, `amenity_listings`.`listing_id` as `pivot_listing_id`, `amenity_listings`.`amenity_id` as `pivot_amenity_id` from `amenities` inner join `amenity_listings` on `amenities`.`id` = `amenity_listings`.`amenity_id` where `amenity_listings`.`listing_id` in (1)

select listing_branches.*, (6371 * acos(cos(radians('32.1234')) * cos(radians(latitude)) * cos(radians(longitude) - radians('30.1245')) + sin(radians('32.1234')) * sin(radians(latitude)))) AS distance from `listing_branches` where `listing_branches`.`listing_id` in (1) order by `distance` asc, CASE WHEN area_id = 3 THEN 0 ELSE 1 END
